news.title: Even in tech hub Shenzhen, China's property market succumbs to chills
news.para: The lack of turnover in Shenzhen's property market and the fallout on the city's real estate brokers stems in part from deliberate policy efforts over the past year by local authorities to make apartment prices more affordable, including requiring higher down payments for second homes and capping resale prices.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji's Joyville to invest Rs 300 crore to build 750 apartments
news.para: ​Joyville, which is a Rs 1,240-crore platform established by business conglomerate Shapoorji Pallonji, ADB, IFC and Actis, has so far launched six housing projects -- three in Pune and one each in Mumbai, Kolkata and Gurugram.

news.title: Digital Core REIT to raise $600 million in Singapore's biggest IPO this year
news.para: The Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT), which owns 10 freehold data centres in the United States and Canada worth around $1.4 billion, is issuing 682 million units at $0.88 per a piece, excluding a greenshoe option worth $47 million.

news.title: Asian Paints to invest Rs 960 crore to expand its manufacturing capacity in Gujarat
news.para: The company has proposed to expand its manufacturing capacity of paint from 130,000 KL to 250,000 KL and resins and emulsions from 32,000 MT to 85,000 MT which will be completed over a period of the next 2-3 years.

news.title: Mumbai’s stuck housing redevelopment projects to get a push
news.para: The state government decides to help resolve issues that have stalled over 550 housing projects by playing a facilitator’s role

news.title: RPS Group to invest Rs 600 crore to build World Trade Centre in Faridabad
news.para: The project -- World Trade Centre (WTC) Faridabad -- will be spread over 7.58 acres of land and with a total leasable/saleable area of one million square feet.

news.title: Greater Noida authority fines 13 builders for encroachment on green belt
news.para: Fine has been imposed against Sam India Olympia, Dream Ville archade, Galaxy plaza, Saya, Aarza square, EM BARC, Gaur City, NXone, Neo town, Nirala estate and Bloom international school.

news.title: Ban on construction, demolition activities in Delhi to continue till further orders
news.para: "Considering the situation, we have decided to extend the ban on construction and demolition activities in Delhi till further orders. Non-polluting construction activities such as plumbing work, interior decoration, electrical work and carpentry are allowed," Gopal Rai said.

news.title: Evergrande shares fall after chairman cuts stake; Fantasia suspends trading
news.para: Evergrande has been scrambling to raise capital as it grapples with more than $300 billion in liabilities and Chinese authorities have told its chairman, Hui Ka Yan, to use some of his personal wealth to help pay bondholders, sources have said.

news.title: MSRDC gets 75% land for new township on Samruddhi corridor
news.para: During his visit in August, MSRDC minister Eknath Shinde had announced the stretch from Nagpur to Shirdi will start for traffic by December end. MSRDC is worried about delay of package-I.

news.title: Rajasthan: 10 urban local bodies fail to give single lease deed
news.para: Among all the local bodies, the Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) has issued highest number (14,884) of lease deeds to the plot owners. It is followed by the urban improvement trust (UIT), Kota and Udaipur, where 5,605 and 4,246 lease deeds have been issued, respectively.

news.title: Adityapur: Lens on business units operating from residential buildings
news.para: Manager of AMC, Debasish Pradhan, said that those commercial establishments set up in buildings which are paying taxes as residential houses will not be given trade licences.

news.title: Gurugram: Housing projects to gensets, GRAP violations continue to attract fines
news.para: On Sunday, the air monitoring station in Teri Gram recorded the highest AQI of 384, followed by Sector 51 with an AQI of 384, Vikas Sadan with an AQI of 361 and Gwal Pahari recording the lowest AQI of 370.

news.title: Gurugram: Review of infrastructure work in DLF colonies on Nov 29
news.para: The MCG chief engineer will review the work as claimed to be completed by developer DLF. Officials from the corporation said, DLF has claimed that most of the work related to roads, drainage and sewerage has been completed.

news.title: Mumbai: SC rejects builder's plea against Wadala flat buyers' refund order
news.para: The SC, however, said, “Even while not entertaining these petitions, we would leave it open for the parties in taking recourse to other appropriate proceedings, including the proposition for settlement, as may be advised and as may be permissible in law.”
